      "description": "Add Zapier Integration for Cross-System Message Ingestion\n\nImplement a Zapier webhook receiver that allows external systems (Slack, Notion, Linear, Jira, HubSpot, etc.) to push messages, notes, and structured data into Krisp's Open Brain persistent memory system and/or Kanban board — without requiring direct API integrations for each source.\n\nRequirements:\n\nWebhook Receiver Endpoint\n- Create a POST /api/integrations/zapier/ingest route secured with a per-user HMAC-signed token or static secret key (consistent with the existing HMAC signing infrastructure)\n- Accept a flexible JSON payload schema covering: message body (required), source system name, author/sender, timestamp, tags, and an optional routing_target field (brain | kanban | both)\n- Validate incoming payloads with Zod, returning structured 400 errors for malformed requests\n\nPayload Routing Logic\n- If routing_target is brain or unspecified: store the message as an Open Brain thought — generate a vector embedding via OpenAI, extract metadata (topic, sentiment, urgency), and persist to the thoughts table\n- If routing_target is kanban: parse the payload and create a new Kanban card with title, description, source label, priority (default: medium), and auto-assigned tag (e.g., \"zapier\")\n- If routing_target is both: execute both pipelines concurrently\n\nZapier-Side Configuration\n- Document the exact Zapier Webhooks (POST) action configuration: endpoint URL, authentication header format, and a canonical payload schema users should map their Zap fields to\n- Provide a sample payload and field mapping guide for at least three common source apps (e.g., Slack, Gmail, Notion)\n\nUser-Facing Setup UI\n- Add a \"Zapier\" section under an Integrations settings page (or extend an existing one if present)\n- Display the user's unique ingest webhook URL with a one-click copy button\n- Allow the user to regenerate the webhook secret, which invalidates the previous token\n- Show a log of the last N ingest events (timestamp, source, routing target, status: success/failed) for debugging\n\nSecurity & Reliability\n- Verify the shared secret on every inbound request before processing; return 401 for invalid signatures\n- Enforce per-user rate limiting on the ingest endpoint consistent with the existing rate-limiting infrastructure\n- Idempotency: include an optional idempotency_key field in the payload to prevent duplicate ingestion if Zapier retries a failed delivery\n- Log all ingest attempts (success and failure) to the existing structured error logging system\n\nEdge Cases to Handle\n- Payload body exceeds token limit for embedding — truncate with a stored warning flag\n- Missing or null message body — reject with a descriptive error\n- routing_target set to kanban but no meaningful title can be derived — fall back to a truncated message body as the card title\n- Clock skew on inbound timestamp — store both the source timestamp and server-received timestamp\n\nPrerequisites\n- Existing HMAC signing infrastructure and rate-limiting middleware must be confirmed compatible with this new route\n- OpenAI embedding pipeline (used by email search) must be reusable for thought ingestion without duplication\n- Personal API Key Management feature must be evaluated as a potential authentication alternative to a separate webhook secret",
